properties.name: PDFARTBOX
properties.description: Crop to ArtBox. The art box defines the extent of the page's meaningful content (including potential white space) as intended by the page's creator.

properties.name: PDFCROPBOX
properties.description: Crop to CropBox. The crop box is the region of the page to display and to print.

properties.name: PDFTRIMBOX
properties.description: Crop to TrimBox. The trim box specifies the positioning of the page's content within the imposition.

properties.name: PDFBLEEDBOX
properties.description: Crop to BleedBox. The bleed box defines the region to which the contents of the page should be clipped when output in a production environment.

properties.name: PDFMEDIABOX
properties.description: Crop to MediaBox. The media box is a natural size of the page. For example, the dimensions of A4 sheet of paper.

properties.name: PDFBOUNDINGBOX
properties.description: Crop to Bounding Box. The bounding box is the rectangle that encloses all text, graphics, and images on the page.
